    <string name="meal_desc0">a dish of Italian origin consisting of a flat, round base of dough baked with a topping of tomato sauce and cheese, typically with added meat or vegetables. cheese and various toppings.</string>
    <string name="meal_desc1">The more tender cuts of beef, from the loin and rib, are cooked quickly, using dry heat, and served whole.</string>
    <string name="meal_desc2">A BLT is a type of sandwich, named for the initials of its primary ingredients, bacon, lettuce and tomato. It can be made with varying recipes according to personal preference.</string>
    <string name="meal_desc3">An empanada is a type of pasty which may consist of meat, cheese, corn, or other ingredients.</string>
    <string name="meal_desc4">A cheeseburger is a hamburger topped with cheese. Traditionally, the slice of cheese is placed on top of the meat patty, but the burger can include many variations in structure, ingredients, and composition.</string>
    <string name="meal_desc5">An omelette or omelet is a dish made from beaten eggs fried with butter or oil in a frying pan (without stirring as in scrambled egg). It is quite common for the omelette to be folded around a filling such as cheese, chives, or vegetables.</string>
    <string name="meal_desc6">Sushi is a Japanese dish of specially prepared vinegared rice, usually with some sugar and salt, combined with a variety of ingredients such as seafood, vegetables, and occasionally tropical fruits.</string>

